Running Python code interactively: import subprocess, sys, textwrap

script_path = '/workspace/solution.py'

test_cases = [
    ("123\n", "77\n"),
    ("250\n", "50\n"),
    ("1\n", "99\n"),
    ("99\n", "1\n"),
    ("100\n", "100\n"),
    ("199\n", "1\n"),
    ("200\n", "100\n"),
    ("299\n", "1\n"),
]

results = []
for inp, expected in test_cases:
    proc = subprocess.run([sys.executable, script_path], input=inp, text=True, capture_output=True)
    out = proc.stdout
    ok = out == expected
    results.append((inp.strip(), out.strip(), expected.strip(), ok, proc.returncode, proc.stderr))

# Print summary
passed = sum(1 for r in results if r[3])
print(f"Passed {passed}/{len(results)} tests")
for r in results:
    print(r)

import subprocess, sys, textwrap

script_path = '/workspace/solution.py'

test_cases = [
    ("123\n", "77\n"),
    ("250\n", "50\n"),
    ("1\n", "99\n"),
    ("99\n", "1\n"),
    ("100\n", "100\n"),
    ("199\n", "1\n"),
    ("200\n", "100\n"),
    ("299\n", "1\n"),
]

results = []
for inp, expected in test_cases:
    proc = subprocess.run([sys.executable, script_path], input=inp, text=True, capture_output=True)
    out = proc.stdout
    ok = out == expected
    results.append((inp.strip(), out.strip(), expected.strip(), ok, proc.returncode, proc.stderr))

# Print summary
passed = sum(1 for r in results if r[3])
print(f"Passed {passed}/{len(results)} tests")
for r in results:
    print(r)
